stories.text: I'm after RG Collingwood's The First Mate's Log. It's in the Intelex Past Masters series of Philosophy texts, which is available online at (most/many?) universities, but I'm not at one. (It seems individuals can't subscribe to that - I just tried.) It's seemingly not on LibGen/Scihub, or archive.org, Gutenberg, or anywhere online, and it seems paper copies start at >$400 for its 130 pages. The book was published in 1939, reprinted in 1994. How can I get hold of it? Paper or ebook is fine. Any ideas? What/where else should I try? I'm willing to pay, but not >$400! Thank you.
